OT of work, complete overhaul even.I think that ground combat mechanics of the original were better, customization of troops is nice, limits are'nt but theres tricks to get around it, you can max troops on every planet except the one thats donating troops to all the others. The combat missions are a nice touch though.Cannot customize starbases! They level like your fighters with tech research which is pretty lame.Once you figure out the strategy of the game, its pretty much wash rinse repeat. Even with randomizing personalities or creating and assigning your own it still breaks down to cheap corvette missle spam early game, shields and DPS or spam fighters mid game and if you make it to late game (without beating the AI or getting one of the victory conditions) canopy shields and chaos cannons (i think thats what they're called - purple pieces) but you propbably wont see a late game unless you start out very isolated. If you want a challenge start next to Vulfar so they can spam you with missile cruisers right as you get a decent fleet going, by then another faction will be♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥at you for trying to steal thier tech or expanding to more than 3 systems and the Vulfar will magically get a better shield tech than you have traded to them.I'd like to see better/more modding, I'm not a big fan of the turn base (I just use pause in the original for planning), fix espionage system, creatable starbases, blockade mechanic/production spamming by AI - theres other ways to make AI challenging than allowing it to ""cheat"". Not much replayability at this time. Hope to see that change.So as much as I like it as a game and it want to be MOO, these lacking features after being released for so long and no action taken by the developer I have to not recommend this game."
