,Not Recommended,252450,33959734,Posted: 1 August,all,Glitchkatten,"The original StarDrive was fun and it was the first 4x strategy game I've ever played. It had some balancing problems though, and the way of moving units around felt slow and was difficult.StarDrive 2 fixed the movement issue, but it made the bad balancing worse and introduced a lot of new bugs that make the game nearly unplayable. I would not recommend this game unless you turn off random encounters and try to be allied with all the other races, or you're willing to have the game go nowhere or set out to bully you into quitting.I'll go through a list of the bugs and issues I encountered:-With random encounters on, the alien forces (not the other races) will show up and ruin all of your progress, and they appear so early in the game that you don't have the technology to defend against them.-The AI can build hundreds of ships and somehow support them all, even while in debt. They can then send these huge fleets to fight you and they will obliterate you no matter what you do.-If you only have a space station in a planet space defense battle, the AI ships will not move to attack. The only exception is if it's the aliens mentioned before, and after they start having the ships with the canopy shields in their fleets, they destroy everything.Those are the biggest issues I've encountered. As for what the game did right:-Everything is turn-based similar to Civilization, and movement still takes time which is handled by the passing of each turn after issuing an order. Researching is handled by turn, building as well, and etc.-The map's planet systems and any other area of the map is in a hex system, which makes it cleaner to look at and easier to find things (for me, at least).-You cannot just research everything in the game.Overall, I can't recommend the game. If the big issues of the game are fixed, then I could recommend it, but until then I cannot."
