,Recommended,252450,15323121,"Posted: 12 April, 2015",all,Static,"I love the game, and you've done a number of things that I've wanted to do to similar games over the years.  First, congrats on taking the MOO2 skeleton and fleshing it out.  Took some guts, and it could have easily been a very bad move.  Second, I really dig the storyline missions and the interactions that come with them.  Good job.  Third, ship building is wonderful, and pretty fast.  A boost to what I expected (I really just want one more feature, changing the arc of fire).  Next, I love the medals for units.  And good job with the revamped ground combat system.  Finally, the small specialty random events (""Your planet is becoming very skilled at building freighters..."") is a brilliant stroke and really adds to the game (is there a way that these bonuses smack you in the face, to make it easier to see, and more difficult to lose a planet to an invasion?)A couple of things:Let us trade, steal, or develop new ship layouts!More tech, racial tech trees, and storylines.  Yeah, I realize I'm asking for addtional content.  I'm happy to pay for good DLC.Let us shift the firing arcs in our ships during the build.  Some arcs on the lateral build sectors should be able to reach fore and/or aft.Better player-side AI management of resource management.  It seems that my planets are always producing food, no matter what.  Even a simple radio box ""New population produces X by default"" would do wonders for play flow.I would love to see a ""Civ-Style"" unit advancement system upon experience boosts.  Let us choose if the unit gets an offense, defense, or other boost.  I love the system there, and I wish we had it here.  It gives units more personality, and attachment.If you miss Masters of Orion 2, get this game.  If you looked at MOO2 and said ""I just wish it had..."", get this game.  If you want a game with decent detail, but no overwhelming micromanaging, get this game."
