76561198006545785,Recommended,252450,15323349,"Posted: 12 April, 2015",all,Rococho Ranger,"IF you keep hearing comparisons to the Civ or Gal Civ series then ignore them, this is a very different kettle of fish.What this game really should be compared to is the Space Empires series.-Turn-based empire building-Real-time space combat-Directly controlable ground combat-Fully customisable troops and shipsStardrive two is basically an updated and much refined version of those games, and for that this game rocks.Reasons to play-The right things are automated.  You have full control, but a lot of tedius micro is done for you by the fraighter system.-The research tree presents you with hard choices, but doesn't mean you can never have the things you don't research.-The planets have several characteristics that make for more hard choices when colonising.  You might desperately need an outpost for your war, but all the planets in that system are small and toxic.  You'll hate it, but love it too.-The whole theme and charictorisation of the races is both cool and comedic.  From samuri bears in combat, to deplomacy with cathulu's kids, to plant people on little trackers and distictive ship designs.  The art style is a gem of the game.-The AI makes you work.  The AI will change its plans.  IF it sees one of your fleets out matches it, they will turn and run, wasting your time if you chase.  They will split into smaller fleets and raid you if you have one big fleet.  They will bombard worlds they can't capture.Reasons not to buy-Sudden onsent of insanity.  See you doctor.  Or of course, if you don't like 4X stratagy.There are still a few relatively minor bugs and bits that could be smoothed a little, but this is the launch version and I expect these things to be ironed out over time.I can't recommend this game enough.  The first stardrive dissappointed me a bit, but I'm glad I gave Zero a second try, and he came through a trooper!"
