76561198005409275,Recommended,252450,15324492,"Posted: 12 April, 2015",all,[WTFH] ragnar_greymane,"Update 6:The real review: the game is, as of patch 1.0d everything that has been promised.The new research-system and exclusive tree is pretty amazing, makes you think what is best for your empire, but not just now, as well as in the future. Trade and negotiation becomes essential to acquire tech, especially espionnage =3 (all you diplomacy-enthusiasts)Planet management is extremely nice, smooth and intuitive. It is some kind of known system, but it fits well in the game.Troop management and equipment adds an individual aspect that I have never experienced in a 4x game before (I played most, beginning with Space Empires IV).The turn system is pretty much the manual version, in my point of view, of the predecessors 5 sec turn instance system. With 8 AI enemies 5 turns, as for my machine, are 5 sec in sum. When needed, this system provides you with planning-possibilities you might and/or will need.To criticise, in my experience, is the 8 ships only build list. You can edit it, ok, but I do not like to manually swap the updated designs for the older ones. Stardrive 1 had the better system with actual and obsolete designs, autoupdates and (for me) never ending design list to choose from.Update: After long hours of intense gameplay, i came to a different understanding. Unique ships are worthy units. You bild them once, they remain in service till they are destroyed or dismissed. Mainline battleships are build often, destroyed often, and updated regularly. Even a humble frigate becomes the cornerstone of a fleet, advances through the system of achievements, collects experience and becomes even more valuable; even a carrier can have experienced fightersquads that are much more survivable and do a better job than freshly produced ones. This feature requires some micromanagement, but time is not a matter.Now for the games key feature: Ship designEverything matters now, not just the sum of components. You can armor them, outfit special characteristics.... Range, angles, everything matters now. Weight and other subsystem-characteristics are detailed and explained within the editor, so no more one-shot ships that need constant supply because their reactors are woefully underrated (engine rating should at least equal power consumption rate). Unfortunately, as of this build, the powergrid system (a rector only supplies power within a limited range) is lost.Damage is applied to different sectors of the ship, is one gone the ship or station is as well.I am continuing to play, have not encountered any bug within 8 hours of gaming.Till the next update!(Playing United Federation)OBSOLETE - (with bugfix link, all credit to original poster of the solution mentioned)First of all, it never started. My desktop (PC) easily fulfills all recommended requirements, but nothing happens. An error pops up and the game ends.Till that bug is removed - DO NOT BUY IT [it is a once in a thousand bug/glitch that occurs while installing, or sth like that. A link to the forum explaining the extremely simple debug - delete a folder in the games user/app.... - is provided, thanks to the guy who identified it. After that, the game runs extremely smooth!Obsolete - first day of possessing Stardrive IIUpdate: now i see the starting screen, but nothing happens. Please wait 0% for 10 minUpdate 2: still waiting for anything to happen..... 1 hour straight - waiting and nothing happens, till my steam client crashed.Update 3: reinstalled for the 4th time. Getting a random file missing file there note. Funny thing: except for microsoft windows security essentials no antivirus is running.... and I do not recieve any conflict or whatsoever info. Still hung at loading screen, but this time zerosumgames took a full minute to vanish.Update 4:looked again and someone found the solution. Testing it right nowhttp://stardrivegame.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=16&t=10997Ok: Crash!!!Update 5: after deleting everything again and again it now starts loading, I am not stuck at 0%. WellllIt seems to be working now. Starting a game for the first time."
