76561198140681915,Recommended,252450,15629771,"Posted: 30 April, 2015",all,Klossk,"This game is nothing short of amazing, it is made by a small indie team (or is it just zero? i'm not sure) but it is just as good as other triple a 4x games.The short answer:my tactical sense is that of a large rockwar owlsmachine gun dinosaursuplifting elephants10/10The long answer:The Good: there are 9 races with unique traits and you can make your own custom race traits. The empire management is simple and easy to learn. The ship combat is a simple order you ships to attack this target or move here, BUT each ship takes damage to a certain part, front back left or right and once all the modules are destroyed, they can attack the core. Destroying the core destroys the ship. So you can maneuver your ships so that they last longer. The ship desgining is easily the most fun part of the game, you drag modules onto a layout of a hull and the positioning can change the part of the ship the shield will protect, the firing arc and more. There are also cool events that can happen, such as an infested ship or finding a planet of dragon people.The Bad: the only victory is to exterminate all the other empires, and the AI acts like they know this. Diplomacy is tough, as the AI tends to ask you for your stuff and threaten war otherwise. Some of the races hull designs are certainly better than others, as the Kulrathi and Opteris Hive seem to have larger ships than the other races. Ground combat is kind of clunky and slow, and I find myself autoing the invasion, even if it makes me lose troops. The Mac version also crashes quite a bit, but it is getting less and less common.BUY this game!"
