76561197970835490,Recommended,252450,15989764,"Posted: 24 May, 2015",all,robblindsay,"After my negative review of Stardrive 1 I thought I'd review this to set the records straight, this game improves on SD1 in every way, every little problem I have with the first one is resolved and more:+ It's stable! Not a single crash, laggy moment or instability.+ The research system is vastly improved and adds a few features I've not seen in a 4x game, including a system that makes diplomacy and espionage very important.+ The ship varieties are nice, the game is very pleasant to look at.+ There's even a little X-com like tactical game for your ground troops+ Random events and regions of space can trigger special research projects that can help your empire+ Freighters and cargo transport has been hugely streamlined, this used to be very frustrating in SD1 having to micromanage all of your freighters.+ Good variety of planet features that give extra depth to the colonisation system including some nods to classic sci-fi.All that being said, there are some things that could have been done a little better:- The sound design suuuucks! from random 'sci-fi beeps' on the tactical map and cheesy 'pew-pew' noises in battles, the sound design could have been so much better, honestly can't remember what the music is like other than I turned it off pretty quickly.- there is a max 100 system limit. the galaxy doesn't feel particularly big, gets crowded quickly with more than 3 opponents.- A couple of balancing issues could use looking atAll in all though, this is a solid 4X game that improves greatly on it's predecessor, pleased to have bought it."
