,Recommended,252450,15335438,"Posted: 13 April, 2015",all,LittleMikey,"As an avid fan of Stardrive 1, I had high standards coming into Stardrive 2. I was surprised to find that the game had changed from a real time strategy to a turn based format, although space combat still happens in real time. The turn based format does not hamper the game flow however, and Stardrive 2 is just as fun as it's predecessor in terms of a space 4X Game.Pros:-Diplomacy system is greatly improved from SD1-Space combat is simple, but effective. Your ships will have multiple weapons and can engage multiple targets at the same time.-Ground combat is now a turn-based system, unlike SD1's ""Land troops on a planet and cross your fingers"" system.-Ship Building has been simplified but still very easy to grasp.-Unique missions and events featuring neautral factions keep the game interesting.-Interesting and diverse factions with different personalities. Factions with similar personality traits get bonuses in diplomacy.Cons:-The game can be very hard for players not familiar with the genre.-The game does not tell you if a planet is sitting idle and not constructing anything. This results in lost production so it's important you keep your build queues full.-Less ability for automation compared to SD1. For example, you cannot tell your scouts to Auto-Explore, or your ships to defend an area."
