76561198021971210,Not Recommended,252450,16749438,"Posted: 27 June, 2015",all,Gwtheyrn,"I would love to recommend this game, but I can't. While I was a huge fan of Stardrive, the sequel just rings hollow.The first title was born of Steam Early Access, and gave the developer a large swath of suggestions, criticism, and feedback during its cycle. The developer would later make it pretty clear that he wasn't terribly fond of getting feedback during development, that there were too many voices in his first game and chose to develop Stardrive 2 behind closed doors.Unfortunately, this is the result of a developer and his hubris stuck in an echo chamber. There's no one to point out flaws in design, resulting in poor decisions being reinforced as good ones inside one's own head, where they become entrenched.Ship design is still good, but not quite as dynamic as SD1. There's far less freedom to build.  Faction customization is expanded. The tech tree is improved, but still not great and leader missions are fun the first time, but grow stale.Outside of that, everything just falls flat. Ground combat is half-baked. Colony management interface is poor. The AI leaves a lot to be desired in both strategic and tactical combat (mathematical advantages are applied to make up for it). Diplomacy is even less useful. The move to a turn-based strategy map has taken away the immediacy of naval engagements.Even with all the bugs, which I can forgive, this culminates into the two most damning critiques of this game:* The game is shallow and has no spirit.* It's flat out boring."
