76561197970216820,Recommended,252450,17587578,"Posted: 17 August, 2015",all,Jim,"This game is the closest to the feel of MOO2 of any other space 4x I've played.Graphics, sound and interface are all first class in my opinion, especially the screens when interacting with alien races.Lots of atmosphere and flavour to the game, the random events (such as one of your arctic planets founding a ski resort), are nice little touches that help give the game it's own personality.The space combat is fun, it's good to see your latest weapon making mincemeat of an enemy fleet, plus as it's real time the battles are over fairly quickly so you don't get bogged down.The land battles have potential, but they aren't up to the same standard as the space battles.Bear in mind this is entirely a war focused game; the alien races are very aggressive and at the moment there is no option to form alliances with a race.You can make a non aggression pact but at best this just buys you some time before you will need to fight that empire.If treated as a ""Total War in space"" type game it's really good. To stand up better against other 4x's I think an expansion may be needed to expand on the non-combat aspects of the game, such as wider diplomancy options and perhaps improved espionage."
