76561198038968845,Recommended,252450,15349573,"Posted: 13 April, 2015",all,NicePotato,"Oh. My god. I'm not saying it's a difficult game. I'm just saying that Dark Souls is like Kirby's Epic Yarn in comparison to this game. That said - once you realise that you need to play it smart and stop thinking in terms of this being a 4X game - the game becomes really interesting.The only way to win is to take an intimate interest in your empire's stats. Like some kind of super micro managing mother. Use all the tools you are given to carve out a bloody path for your empire to success, because otherwise someone else will carve a bloody and desperate path right through your face.Pros:The UI is buttload better than most of the other space strategy games out there. It's not great. It's just better than most, which I call a pro.The management of the planets and ships makes sense. I've yet to go ""Oh. I wish I could do that.""Customising the loadout of your ships both works great and is absolutely vital to victory. Because only you know what kind of ship you need for what kind of scenario. Need a pure tank to absorb the initial attack and then a bunch of fighters slam into the enemy dealing the real damage? You gotta make it happen yourself. And you can. And it's awesome.Cons:The tutorial. I sort of didn't want to put it as a con, because it's not bad compared to other space strategy games. But it's still narration. ""Do this, this happens."" That said - it's short, to the point and gives you the important stuff. As someone who never pays attention to tutorials, this one worked well enough to get me into it.The difficulty is a bit odd. On the lowest difficulty I got my♥♥♥♥♥handed to me. This was until I started customising my ships, but even so. The lowest difficult is supposed to be a ""try this button and see what it does."" kind of affair, not ""you want easy? You can't handle easy. Here, have some insanity.""Overall - if you want a challenge, and a good space empire game, I say grab this one."
