76561198007896071,Recommended,252450,15363276,"Posted: 14 April, 2015",all,Slater86,"SD2 is a difficult 4x strategy game with homicidal AI and some very good game mechanics. Overall the game is very solid but in its current state if falls just short of a classic. A must have for space strategy fan boys, not a good buy for a casual gamer or those new to the genre.The Good:* Customizable options for the factions and starships lends to great immersion. I have made plenty of flagship battle heavy titans that get smashed because I didn't place armor in the right places or had too many spinal mounts that could hit anything far away but the big ship couldn't turn fast enough to handle flank attacks.* Graphics are awesome. Clicking on planets and watching the cities light up on the dark side increase with population is a nice touch. Ships blow up into several smaller pieces and actually come apart instead of an explosion cloud animation.* Space battles tend to devolve into choatic melees despite the most careful planning and ship design ( I consider this a realistic plus some micromangers may get frustrated with the lack of form in battle) A formation button would be a plus.The Bad:* Homicadal AI that will attack at immediately when weakness is shown* AI sends massive doom fleets that are kinda of fun to destroy with some well built smaller fleets, but it is easy to be get overwhelmed* Some characters cause some serious headaches. Watch your♥♥♥♥♥if you hire Zapp Groening, because the AI will go ape♥♥♥♥♥♥ (-20 diplo for a 30% firepower bump)* Ground combat seems a bit underwhelming. Troops are determined by population so 6 soldiers defending a world of 6 billion doesn't seem right in scale.* Tech tree are based on difficult choices. Each category has one of three options. If you just start playing and researching blind you will find that you have a broken economy and a disfunctional empire mid game.Summary:* Active community with a developer who reads the damn forums and reacts with frequent patches* Hard but satisfying when you develop a winning reciepe* A beautiful game with great FPS for the graphics (34 hours in no CTD)* A lot of bang for 30 bucks* Samurai Space Bears"
