r to what you can already experience in Distant Worlds.This way when you decide to colonize say Titan, you send a colony ship to Saturn and it will pop up a menu in which you can look Saturn and its moons.Colonizing a Gas Giant is something more practical after you develop matter alteration technology, although you should be able to mine it before colonize it. Similar you should be able to mine Asteroids and worlds without an atmosphere before you can colonize it. Mining should allow you to gain resources, thus increase income and gain access to valuable resources, but you won't be able to build anything or have a thriving population until you colonize it. This could be done with a constructor.Eventually you should be able to colonize a star, but this is done in steps after you have the technology to colonize a gas giant, starting with Brown Dwarfs, then Red Dwarfs, then Average Stars, then Giant Stars, then White Dwarfs, then Supergiants, and then Neutron Stars.What is this technology. Well you can create floating population centers similar to the one in Star Wars Episode V. This also means there should be different types of gas giants. Helium, Hydrogen, Methane and Oxygen types. Hydrogen is easiest to synthesize, making it the easiest to colonize when you got the right tech. Helium is difficult, but offers an easier abundance of Helium-3. Methane types also offer valuable resources and oxygen types are more practical for environmental residences, because you already have air you can breathe, well with minimal adjustments considered of course.As for Stars, we are talking about a dyson sphere. Take everything concerning a gas giant and just multiple your gains a hundred fold at least.You also need those sorts of anomalies you can mine like in Galactic Civilization 3. Antimatter is easier to acquire from a black hole and that needs to be a resource you should acquire. I suggest looking at Distant Worlds, Endless Space and Galactic Civilizations 3 to see what types of resources should be considered as strategic for certain uses necessary in the game."
